    {
        "id": 376,
        "slug": "pharmacy",
        "title": "Pharmacy",
        "url": "https://cmcenters.org/health-services/pharmacy/",
        "date": "2023-07-18 04:18:12",
        "modified": "2024-04-09 07:57:19",
        "excerpt": "",
        "content": "<p>The CMC Pharmacy makes it easier to get the medications you need. We participate in the federal 340B Drug Pricing Program to provide our patients with discounted prescriptions through our on-site pharmacies.</p>\r\n<p>If you are having trouble obtaining your medication at any local pharmacy, you can transfer your medications to our in-house pharmacies listed below.</p>\r\n<p>3 Easy Steps for Medication Refills:</p>\r\n<ul><li>Call your pharmacy\r\n</li><li>Allow up to 48 hours\r\n    </li><li>Pick up your medication promptly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember:</p>\r\n<ul><li>Always use the latest prescription number on your medication bottle when calling your pharmacy for refills\r\n</li><li>Often, your refill is waiting for you. Ask your pharmacy to check\r\n</li><li>Pick up your medication promptly. The pharmacy may place it back into stock after 7 days\r\n</li><li>You can call or text an Rx Refill Team Member at (209) 636-5513, with staff available to speak with you Monday-Friday, 8:30 a.m. – 4:30 p.m.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For your SAFETY, pain medication refills require a monthly appointment with your primary care provider and cannot be refilled by phone or fax.</p>",
        "thumbnail": "/img/2024__03__CMC-Services-Pharmacy.jpg",
        "meta": {
            "ignyte_locations[]": {
